    "created_at": "2016-05-22T07:37:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-22T07:37:11Z",
    "body": "The `remote` object does support non-native Promise, but the name of class has to be `Promise`, otherwise it is impossible to confirm whether the object is an Promise. In your case it doesn't work because you are using the `bluebird` object directly, and Electron doesn't know it is a Promise.\n"
